While we strive to protect the information provided to our Partners, we have no direct control over their use of the collected information and therefore you acknowledge that we are not liable for any third-party privacy breach and that our liability for our Partner breaches is limited to the amount we are able to receive as indemnification from our Partners (legal costs exempted).
4.1.2 Other players and users, as social features are an important component of our games. Users may, for example, see your profile data, in-game activities and read the messages you have posted. Please note that information that you voluntarily make public in your user profile, or which you disclose by posting comments will be publicly available and viewable by others;
4.1.3 Any competent law enforcement body, regulatory authority, government agency, the court of law or another third party where we believe disclosure is necessary (i) as a matter of applicable law or regulation, (ii) to exercise, establish or defend our legal rights, or (iii) to protect your vital interests or those of any other person;
4.1.4 With a potential or actual buyer (and its agents and advisers) in connection with any proposed or actual purchase, merger, or acquisition of any part of our business, provided that we inform the buyer it must use your personal information solely for the purposes disclosed in this Privacy Policy. If we (or substantially all of our assets) are acquired by a third party, personal information held by us about our users will be one of the transferred assets;
4.1.5 Other persons to process your personal information for us based on our instructions and in compliance with this Privacy Policy.
4.2 We require high standards of confidentiality from such third parties. If any personal information that we collect from you is provided to third parties outside the European Economic Area (EEA) we will ensure appropriate safeguards are in places, such as the standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission or the Privacy Shield mechanism.
4.3 We may pass aggregated information to third parties about how our users use our Service but this will not include information that could be used to identify you.
5. WHERE WE STORE YOUR INFORMATION, DATA RETENTION
5.1 We take appropriate organizational and technical measures to protect the personal information that we hold. Specific technical measures include data anonymization, a data retention policy, and encryption of data in transit. We limit access to your personal information to those who we believe reasonably need to come into contact with that information in order to carry out their jobs.
5.2 The data that we collect from you may be transferred to and stored at, a destination outside the European Economic Area (
EEA
). It may also be processed by staff operating outside the EEA who work for us, one of our associated companies or a third party engaged by us. In this event, we will ensure appropriate safeguards are in places, such as the approved standard contractual clauses or the Privacy Shield. We will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your personal information is treated securely at all times and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
5.3 The transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although we consider the sensitivity of the personal information we collect, process, and store and will do our best to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee the security of your information transmitted to our Service and any transmission is at your own risk.
5.4
We may retain your personal information
in order to fulfill any of the Services we provide or to comply with applicable legislation, regulatory requests, and relevant orders from competent courts. The length of time we will hold or store your personal information will depend on the services we perform for you and how long you require these and generally falls into the following categories:
5.4.1 Game data backups, logs, chat history, etc., containing your personal data – shall be retained for up to 14 days; or
5.4.2 Any personal data, collected and retained by us (e.g. personalized game progress, payment information, device information, etc.) – shall be deleted upon your written request sent to us or within 7 years after your last use of Service, whichever is earlier; or
5.4.3 Any personal data, collected and retained by us (e.g. personalized game progress, payment information, device information, etc.) – shall be deleted upon ceasing of a particular game operation within 6 months;
6. COMPLIANCE AND COOPERATION WITH REGULATORS, LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING PERSONAL DATA
6.1 We regularly review this Privacy Policy and make sure that we process your information in ways that comply with it.
6.1.1 Data transfers: we use servers around the world and your information may be processed on servers located outside of the country where you live. Regardless of where your information is processed, we apply the same protections described in this Privacy Policy and the European requirements for the transfer of your information, as outlined above.
6.1.2 If GDPR applies to the processing of your information, we provide the controls described in this Privacy Policy so you can exercise your right to request access to, update, remove, and restrict the processing of your information. You may also object to the processing of your information in certain circumstances. For more information on your rights, see Section 11 below.
6.2 We process your information for the purposes described in this policy,
based on these legal grounds
:
6.2.1 With your consent. We or our service providers/partners may ask for your consent to process your information for specific purposes (such as for example, direct marketing) and you may withdraw your consent at any time;
6.2.2 When pursuing legitimate interests. We process your information for our legitimate business interests while applying safeguards that protect your privacy. This means we process your information for things like:
Providing, maintaining, and improving our Services to meet the needs of our users;
Developing new products and features;
Detecting, preventing, or otherwise addressing fraud, abuse, security, or technical issues with our websites; and,
Protecting against harm to the rights, property, or safety of us or our users, or the public as required or permitted by law;
Providing you with special in-game offers and rewards.
6.2.3 When entering into or performing a contract. We process your data to provide a Service you have asked for (for example, make a game available to you, provide customer support, etc.); and,
6.2.4 When complying with legal obligations. We will process your data when we have a legal obligation to do so, for example, if we are responding to a legal process or an enforceable governmental request.
6.3 If you have questions about our legal basis for processing information, you may contact us at
support@littlebit.games
. You can contact your local data protection authority if you have concerns regarding your rights under local law or would like to complain.
7. COOKIES
7.1 We use cookies and similar technologies such as local storage within our apps to provide and optimize our Service. You can control which cookies you get and which you keep on your device through your browser settings. Unless you have adjusted your browser settings so that it will refuse our cookies, our system will issue cookies when you visit our website. However, if you do not accept cookies you may not be able to take advantage of many of the special features of the Service.
7.2 We use cookies to keep track of the pages you and other users have been to on our Service. Cookies enable us to recognize you and remember important information that will make your use of our Service more convenient (e.g. by remembering your user preferences).
7.3 You can disable cookies on your device or set your device to alert you when cookies are being sent to your device; however, disabling cookies may affect your ability to use the Services.
8. LINKS
Our Service may contain links to and from other websites and Services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of any third-party sites. Please check the individual Privacy Policy of any such websites or Services before you submit any personal information to them.
9. ADVERTISERS
Please note that we show third party advertising in our games and also advertise our Services via third parties. We wanted to provide you with more detail about how we use the information for advertising, both in-game and on other third-party properties.
When you view ads on LBP’s properties
To enable us to show in-game ads we may send your advertising ID, IP-address, and other information to advertisers (or ad networks) to enable them to find appropriate ads to serve to you in our games and on third-party properties. You can control and limit our use of your advertising ID in your device settings. LBP does not control which specific ads are shown in our games (this is controlled by ad networks) but we do blacklist certain categories of ads.
Advertising IDs are used by the ad networks for a number of purposes, for example, to:
limit the number of times you see the same ad;
ensure they are dealing with humans/with real devices and not automated bots;
to serve you with advertisements likely to be relevant to you;
other brands buy advertisement placement via an ad network or ad exchange to advertise their products in LBP’s games. The ad network or ad exchange acts as an intermediary between the other game companies and LBP. In order for an ad network to charge the company buying the ad, clicks from the ad, and potentially installs of other developers’ applications party apps are tracked. Views, clicks, installs, and similar events from ads are measured using Advertiser ID.
IP-address is typically used by advertisers to broadly see the general geographic area you are coming from for example country, state, and sometimes at the city level.
When you view LBP’s ads on third party services
Little Bit Publishing also advertises its games in other apps by asking ad networks to serve its ads to audiences that will be interested in them. The advertising IDs are used by the ad networks for a number of purposes, including, for example, to measure ad effectiveness (looking at aggregated views, clicks and installs it generates through its advertising in other publishers’ games). Advertising IDs are also used to track views, clicks, installs, and other similar events from ads.
You can opt-out of interest-based advertising on mobile applications by changing the privacy settings of your device and selecting "limit ad tracking" (Apple iOS) or "opt-out of interest-based ads" (Android).
10. KEEPING YOUR ACCOUNT SECURE
10.1 Where we have given you (or where you have chosen) a password which enables you to access certain parts of the Service, you are responsible for keeping this password confidential and you are responsible for any misuse of such information. You must change your password on a regular basis and must not share your password with anyone.
10.2 You are solely responsible for the security and confidentiality of your account. Please ensure that you do not allow anyone else to access the Service in your name and sign off after you have finished accessing your account.
10.3 You are responsible for all orders, and for the accuracy of all information, sent via the internet using your user ID, password, or any other personal identification used to identify you on the Services.
11. YOUR RIGHTS
11.1 You have the following rights over the personal information we hold about you:
(a)
to access, correct, update or request deletion
of your personal information;
(b)
to object to the processing
of your personal information (which is processed on the grounds of legitimate interests), ask us to
restrict processing
of your personal information or
request
portability
of your personal information (request that data which you have provided to us is provided to you, so you can transfer this to another data controller);
(c) to opt-out of personalized offers based on your in-game activities and behavior and to object to use your personal information for direct marketing purposes;
(d) if we are processing your personal information with your consent, you can
withdraw your consent
at any time. Withdrawing your consent will not affect the lawfulness of any processing we conducted prior to your withdrawal, nor will it affect the processing of your personal information conducted in reliance on lawful processing grounds other than consent.
(e) you have
the right to complain
to a data protection authority about our collection and use of your personal information. For more information, please contact your local data protection authority.
You may exercise all the above-mentioned rights by creating an in-game support ticket or by contacting us using the details at the "How to Contact Us" section below.
You can control and limit the nature of personal information that we collect and process about you in a number of ways. For example, you can disconnect your social media account from our games or control your social media privacy settings to limit the information shared with us. You could also reset your mobile advertising identifier or limit ad tracking altogether using the settings on your device. You could also limit or disable the use of cookies (or similar technologies).
We will respond to all requests we receive from individuals wishing to exercise their data protection rights in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
11.2 If you have any questions, would like to contact us about the processing of your information or wish to exercise your rights as described above, you may contact us at
support@littlebit.games
. We may require evidence of your identity before we are able to act on your request.
11.3 You may "opt-out" from the collection of your personal information by contacting us at
support@littlebit.games
.
12. CHANGES TO OUR PRIVACY POLICY
We occasionally modify our Privacy Policy and any changes we may make to it in the future will be posted on this page and, where necessary, may be communicated to you.
